The Nigeria Deposit Insurance Corporation (NDIC) has  disclosed that  it has refunded N220 billion to 535,815 depositors, creditors and shareholders of failed banks in the country as of December 29, 2021. The managing director, Bello Hassan, stated this at the ‘NDIC Day’ at the ongoing 33rd Enugu International Trade Fair in Enugu yesterday. Hassan stated that the amount included insured and uninsured sums, adding that the corporation had declared full payment of insured and uninsured sums to depositors of 18 banks in-liquidation. “This implies that the corporation has realised liquidation dividends to pay all depositors of the banks who present themselves for payment,” he said. The fair was organized by the Enugu Chamber of Commerce Industries, Mines & Agriculture with the theme: “Opening up Nigerian business windows for competitiveness in the emerging global market”.  